  "response": "The Stark Malibu mansion, known as the Stark residence in the Iron Man movies, is a fictional creation and does not exist in real life. However, the exterior shots of the mansion were filmed at a real location called the \"El Fureidis\" estate in Malibu, California. This property was designed by architect Paul Williams in the 1960s and has distinctive Mediterranean-style architecture. While the mansion itself is not a real residence of Tony Stark, the scenes are brought to life through a combination of real-world locations and CGI effects to fit the film's narrative and aesthetics.",
